content:
You can use tables to get a view of the data that is close to the underlying dataset. With values, compare, and pivot tables, CRM Analytics gives you options for both managing the view of data and manipulating it to expose fresh insights.

Manage the View of Data in a Values Table
The values table displays all columns in your dataset. You can customize the view of columns and sort row values using any column except for the index column.

Navigate Compare Table Columns
Create columns and navigate between existing ones using clicks or keystrokes.

Organize and Summarize Data in a Pivot Table
Arrange data by a key dimension to identify patterns quickly. Group pivoted data further, add row and column totals, subtotals, and grand totals, and sort measures for ranking in ascending or descending order (beta).

Add Custom Formulas to Columns
Define custom formulas using the column editor. View measures side by side, perform math across columns and rows, and create labels with string values.

Window Functions Available in the Compare Table
Use window functions from the function menu to save time writing SAQL code.

Use Raw Field Names in Query Formulas
Reference measure and group columns by name when writing compare-table formulas. Use formula pickers to enter SAQL formulas quickly.

Table Properties
Control a table's appearance using table properties.

Column Properties
Jazz up columns with conditional formatting, text alignment, and text styles. Set data types as bars or display data in text format.
title: Explore Data with CRM Analytics Tables
